spanGrp.span: ‘It is told that the bus only comes from Buenos Aires;
Je wapage je bus bönẽ bötö-gẽu-nẽ mãu dia Buenos Aires
it comes, goes by all the way up to San Vicente.
je bötö-gẽu kögẽu juei San Bisente

spanGrp.span: Then it comes from Buenos Aires
There one goes to Santa Maria;
there is no bus to Santa Maria.

u.seg: FM_Filler FM_Filler FM_Filler FM_Filler FM_Filler FM_Filler

spanGrp.span: It comes around here; here is still Ujarraz.
Kã'u jiska í tsõ ĩã jirö Ujarras
It goes to Guanacaste and San Vicente.
The bus picks up people in the morning;
je wa bus mĩ-gẽu Bus shkö-gẽ siñira pe tsõ

spanGrp.span: at dawn, at noon and at dusk, at four.’
Kã'ñir eee… siñira kã'wö mediodia kã'wö las/ kã'wö mãu las kuatro
